about.summary: Provides functions to analyse overdispersed counts or proportions.  These functions should be considered as complements to more sophisticated methods such as generalized estimating equations (GEE) or generalized linear mixed effect models (GLMM). aods3 is an S3 re-implementation of the deprecated S4 package aod.

Provides functions to analyse overdispersed counts or proportions.  These functions should be considered as complements to more sophisticated methods such as generalized estimating equations (GEE) or generalized linear mixed effect models (GLMM). aods3 is an S3 re-implementation of the deprecated S4 package aod.

name: r-aods3
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.4-1.2' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-aods3
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/aods3_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/aods3/aods3_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 8d5cfcea7c971ad5ebc9e87c4b7316dbc797ce86285f02514d84296e4feea465

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('aods3')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('aods3')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=aods3
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: Provides functions to analyse overdispersed counts or proportions.  These functions
    should be considered as complements to more sophisticated methods such as generalized
    estimating equations (GEE) or generalized linear mixed effect models (GLMM). aods3
    is an S3 re-implementation of the deprecated S4 package aod.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
